Hi Steve.  I think being a physical part of the process is what draws me to manual radio 
sweep, and what made me try SS2 with the allophones.  I think our unconscious decisions 
about how fast or slow to move the dial/slider, and when to change directions, can help 
improve communication.  But that&#39;s just been my experience.  I know some others do not 
feel the same.  

I will say I find it&#39;s a little easier to listen realtime to the responses when I&#39;m not manually 
sweeping, as that can be a bit like jumping up and down on one foot while patting my 
head with one hand and rubbing my tummy with the other!  LOL.  

Margaret

